1 to subsection (a) of this section and make recommendations
2 to the joint education interim committee, including, but
3 not limited to, whether the limitation on the number of
4 school districts that may be placed in educational
5 bankruptcy pursuant to W.S. 21-2-1003(h) should be
6 modified. The joint education interim committee shall
7 report its recommendations, if any, to the legislature
8 during the immediately succeeding legislative session.
9
10 (h) The state superintendent of public instruction
11 shall promulgate rules necessary to administer this
12 section.
